The following classes accept all types that extend the `Document` interface:

- [Collection](https://mongodb.github.io/node-mongodb-native/7.1/classes/Collection.html)

- [ChangeStream](https://mongodb.github.io/node-mongodb-native/7.1/classes/ChangeStream.html)

You can pass a type parameter that extends the `Document` interface like this:

```typescript
interface Pet {
  name: string;
  age: number;
}

const database = client.db("<your database>");
const collection = database.collection<Pet>("<your collection>");

```

> **Important:**&#x20;
>
> Keys Not in Type Parameter Receive 
>
> `any`
>
>  Type
>
> Keys not listed in your specified type parameter receive the `any` type.
> The following code snippet demonstrates this behavior:
>
> ```typescript
> interface User {
>   email: string;
> }
>
> const database = client.db("<your database>");
> const myColl = db.collection<User>("<your collection>");
> myColl.find({ age: "Accepts any type!" });
> ```

